Preheat oven to temperature 375 degrees F. Cook noodles in a large pan of boiling water 5-7 minutes, or until almost tender. Drain. Saute onion and sausage in a heavy nonstick skillet over medium high heat 5-7 minutes, until brown. Stir frequently to break up meat. Remove from heat. Discard drippings. Stir noodles and next 5 ingredients into sausage. Add salt and pepper to taste. Transfer to a buttered casserole dish and spread evenly. Bake in preheated oven for 35 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.